			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">When I calculate HP/tic regen, I take the pets HP into account.  I always use this basic formula
<br />

<br />
((per tic regen value)/(Total pet HP)) = ((% regen per tic)/(100))
<br />

<br />
You just substitute the one value you don't know and then solve for it using basic Algebra.   So no worries about changing pet HP, it's accounted for.
<br />

<br />
Another way I test HP and Regen is to use /pet hold and have another mage nuke my pet for 2k.  Record what HP % he drops down to.  Then use the following equation...
<br />
2000/X = (% HP lost)/100
<br />

<br />
So if the pet starts at 100% HP then ends up at 40% after the nuke, this would be your equation...
<br />
2000/X = 60/100, solving for X we get, (2000*100)/60 = X, where X = 3333
<br />

<br />
Now testing regen is very simple too.  Start a timer as soon as the other mage lands that nuke for 2k.  Say the pet hits full HP again in 70 seconds.  That would be 2000HP/70 seconds, which works out to 28.57 HP/sec.  Now multiply that by 6 and you get 171 HP/tic regen.
<br />

<br />
now <span style="font-weight: bold">IF</span> the last reply I made was correct with all the numbers on HP, regen % etc. for the GoDS focused Earth pet, then I believe that means your pet would have...
<br />

<br />
Higher DPS with GoDS focus
<br />
Higher HP with GoDS focus
<br />
Higher Clear Hate list Regen with DPoC focus
<br />

<br />
As for which focus item is better in what situation, it comes down to which of those stats matters the most for that situation.  Now remember, I'm not 100% sure about the numbers I posted for the GoDS focused Earth pets.  I don't have the GoDS, I just have the DPoC so I have tested that.  All the information I got for the GoDS I got from reading these boards.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Eandori (Retired)</a>
