				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From my experience only:
<br />

<br />
In a PVE environment, the pet takes on the resists of its owner. Innate resistances, such as water to poison attacks, are disregarded. 
<br />

<br />
However, in PVP environment, pets have very little resistances if any at all. Non lure spells will land on any pet very frequently. However, it appears in pvp that pets regain a portion of their natural resistances (such as earth to disease , water to poison , fire to fire). 
<br />

<br />
I'll have to take some tests to confirm these suspcisions. However, time and time again I have experienced pets being able to withstand aoe's of worse than -250 resist adjust when the owner's saves are high. However, as a cleric I am able to easily nuke down pets even when their owners have extremely high magic resists.
<br />

<br />
More information to come.<br />_________________<br /><i>"...They had triumphed where all others before them had failed, they had slain the Legendary Kerafyrm. As the victors departed the ancient tomb, rumors began to spread across the world of Rallos Zek. Rumors became Stories. Stories became Legend..."</i>
<br />

<br />
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=437975" target="blank"><span style="font-weight: bold"> Exarch Raolador Viriditas</span></A>
<br />

<br />
Archon of <A HREF="http://wudan.waster.net" target="blank">Wudan</a>
<br />
Rallos Zek</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
